commands.mtz_companions.exploration_freq: [%.2f] refers to a floating point number between 0.0 and 1.0; a measure of exploration frequency.
commands.mtz_companions.gather.added: [%1$s] is a number, [%2$s] is the name of an item. Example: `Added [5] [cobblestone] to items to gather.`
commands.mtz_companions.gather.already_h: [%1$s] is a number, [%2$s] is the name of an item. Example: `Target companion's inventory already contains 5 cobblestone. Please specify a larger amount.`
commands.mtz_companions.set_home.success: [%1$s] is a companion name, [%2$s] are block coordinates.
companion.mtz_companions.respawn.anchor: [%1$s] is a companion name, [%2$s] are block coordinates.
companion.mtz_companions.respawn.bed: [%1$s] is a companion name, [%2$s] are block coordinates.
companion.mtz_companions.set_spawn: [%1$s] is a companion name, [%2$s] are block coordinates.
